  "text": "All effectiveness assessments were conducted at month 4. The primary effectiveness measure was the mean change from baseline on the FACE-Q 10-item Satisfaction with Facial Appearance Overall Scale. [CITATION_1] 32 Patients completed the scale in writing in the treating investigator's office. Each item was evaluated on a 4-point scale (very dissatisfied to very satisfied). Additional FACE-Q assessments, including the FACE-Q Aging Appearance Appraisal, FACE-Q Age Appraisal Visual Analog Scale, FACE-Q Social Confidence Scale, and FACE-Q Psychological Well-Being Scale, were evaluated, and results are reported separately.",
